# API Patterns

## Server (Fastify)

All API endpoints live in `apps/server/src/routes/`. Each route file exports an async plugin function.

### Adding a New Endpoint

1. Create or update a route file in `apps/server/src/routes/`
2. **Always define a schema** for Swagger generation:

```typescript
app.get("/resource", {
  schema: {
    description: "What this endpoint does",
    tags: ["resource"],
    querystring: { /* ... */ },
    response: {
      200: { type: "object", properties: { /* ... */ } },
    },
  },
}, async (request, reply) => { /* ... */ });
```

3. Register the route in `apps/server/src/app.ts`
4. Verify the endpoint appears in Swagger UI at `http://localhost:3001/docs`

### Route Organization

- Group related endpoints in a single file (e.g., `users.ts` has GET/POST/PATCH/DELETE)
- Use Fastify route prefixes: `app.register(userRoutes, { prefix: "/api" })`
- Use `schemas/` directory for shared Zod schemas

## Frontend (React Query Hooks)

Every API call on the frontend MUST use React Query via a custom hook.

### Hook File Convention

- Location: `src/hooks/` (in web/admin) or `hooks/` (in react-native)
- One hook per file: `use-get-users.ts`, `use-create-post.ts`
- File naming: kebab-case matching the hook name

### Hook Naming

- Queries: `useGet[Resource]` or `useList[Resources]` (e.g., `useGetUser`, `useListPosts`)
- Mutations: `use[Verb][Resource]` (e.g., `useCreatePost`, `useUpdateUser`, `useDeletePost`)

### Hook Template (Query)

```typescript
import { useQuery } from "@tanstack/react-query";

export function useGetUsers() {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ["users"],
    queryFn: async () => {
      const res = await fetch("/api/users");
      if (!res.ok) throw new Error("Failed to fetch users");
      return res.json();
    },
  });
}
```

### Hook Template (Mutation)

```typescript
import { useMutation, useQueryClient } from "@tanstack/react-query";

export function useCreateUser() {
  const queryClient = useQueryClient();
  return useMutation({
    mutationFn: async (data: { email: string; name: string }) => {
      const res = await fetch("/api/users", {
        method: "POST",
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
        body: JSON.stringify(data),
      });
      if (!res.ok) throw new Error("Failed to create user");
      return res.json();
    },
    onSuccess: () => {
      queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ["users"] });
    },
  });
}
```

## Checklist for Any API Change

- [ ] Endpoint has schema defined (for Swagger)
- [ ] React Query hook created/updated in all consuming apps
- [ ] Types are consistent between server response and frontend hook
